trans-unit.source: Provides information that accessibility applications use to adjust the user interface of a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem"></xref> for users with impairments.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.ToolStripItemAccessibleObject"></xref> class.
The <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem"></xref> that owns this <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.ToolStripItemAccessibleObject"></xref>.
The ownerItem parameter is `null`.

Adds a <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.ToolStripItemAccessibleObject.State"></xref> if <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates"></xref> is <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates.None"></xref>.
One of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates"></xref> values other than <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates.None"></xref>.
Gets the bounds of the accessible object, in screen coordinates.
An object of type <xref href="System.Drawing.Rectangle"></xref> representing the bounds.
Gets a string that describes the default action of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem"></xref>.
A description of the default action of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem"></xref>.
Gets the description of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Control.ControlAccessibleObject"></xref>.
A string describing the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ToolStripItem.ToolStripItemAccessibleObject"></xref>.
Performs the default action associated with this accessible object.
Gets an identifier for a Help topic and the path to the Help file associated with this accessible object.
When this method returns, contains a string that represents the path to the Help file associated with this accessible object.
This parameter is passed without being initialized.
An identifier for a Help topic, or -1 if there is no Help topic.
On return, the fileName parameter will contain the path to the Help file associated with this accessible object, or `null` if there is no `IAccessible` interface specified.
Gets the description of what the object does or how the object is used.
A string describing what the object does or how the object is used.
Gets the shortcut key or access key for the accessible object.
The shortcut key or access key for the accessible object, or `null` if there is no shortcut key associated with the object.
Gets or sets the name of the accessible object.
The object name, or `null` if the property has not been set.
Navigates to another accessible object.
One of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleNavigation"></xref> values.
An <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleObject"></xref> that represents one of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleNavigation"></xref> values.
Gets or sets the parent of an accessible object.
An object of type <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleObject"></xref> representing the parent.
Gets the role of this accessible object.
One of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleRole"></xref> values.
Gets the state of this accessible object.
One of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates"></xref> values, or <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates.None"></xref> if no state has been set.
Returns a string that represents the current object.
A string that represents the current object.
